mv — move/rename files and directories

SYNOPSIS
  mv SRC... DST

DESCRIPTION
  Renames SRC to DST when both live on the same OC filesystem
  (vfs.rename, an O(1) directory-entry swap). When SRC and DST sit on
  different mounts, mv falls back to a full copy followed by removal of
  the source — slower, but the result is identical.

  As with cp, if DST is a directory each SRC is moved into it.

EXAMPLES
  mv old.txt new.txt
  mv * /home/archive/

SEE ALSO
  cp(1), rm(1)
